		<title>17 Water-Farm Uses.</title>
		<content>In farm areas water is needed for:     
             1.Cooling milk.           
             2.Washing.                
             3.Drinking water for cows.
Cows drink 30 gallons per 24 hours-pro-
blem for farmers because water from so-
uth Staffs costs 85p per 1000 gallons. 
Natural supplies are now being         
exploited where possible to supplement 
-Union Hall Farm.                      
-Compton Hall Farm.                    
-Potters Cross Farm(see Housing).      
No rivers in our D block.              
Fish ponds filled in(High Trees).      
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
